span.p:
Initialize:
current_cell = world_to_grid(entry_point)
step.x = sign(ray.direction.x)
step.y = sign(ray.direction.y)
step.z = sign(ray.direction.z)

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Calculate t_delta (constant):
t_delta.x = |cell_size / ray.direction.x|
t_delta.y = |cell_size / ray.direction.y|
t_delta.z = |cell_size / ray.direction.z|
These never change!

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Calculate t_max (initial):
next_boundary = cell_corner + step * cell_size
t_max.x = (next_boundary.x - ray_pos.x) / ray.dir.x
t_max.y = (next_boundary.y - ray_pos.y) / ray.dir.y
t_max.z = (next_boundary.z - ray_pos.z) / ray.dir.z

span.p:
Get fine cell data:
idx = current_cell.x +
current_cell.y * nx +
current_cell.z * nx * ny
cell = fine_cells[idx]
count = cell.count

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
For j = 0 to count:
obj_id = cell.object_indices[j]
IF obj_id < num_boxes:
test box
ELSE:
test triangle[obj_id - num_boxes]
Keep closest hit
